This movie was always one step ahead of me
I remember wanting to take off half a star for how long this movie is, but I wasn’t sure if that’s ethical

The score set a much different tone than what I expected. There were also a few shot discontinuities, and I wanted more of a conclusion with the mayor and townspeople, but it had good jump scares and was kinda fun

Tough to get through for the modern viewer, especially since I was watching by myself (spread over 3 days). Definitely a lot of interesting framing, moving shots, and moving people. It has a fairly simple plot, and I’d only recommend this if you’re studying film or have time to kill and specifically want to watch an old Japanese movie
